  22 @attr.s
  23 class WindowsFinder(BaseFinder):
  24     paths = attr.ib(default=attr.Factory(list), type=list)
  25     version_list = attr.ib(default=attr.Factory(list), type=list)
  26     _versions = attr.ib()  # type: DefaultDict[Tuple, PathEntry]
  27     _pythons = attr.ib()  # type: DefaultDict[str, PathEntry]

  29     def find_all_python_versions(
  30         self,
  31         major=None,  # type: Optional[Union[str, int]]
  32         minor=None,  # type: Optional[int]
  33         patch=None,  # type: Optional[int]
  34         pre=None,  # type: Optional[bool]
  35         dev=None,  # type: Optional[bool]
  36         arch=None,  # type: Optional[str]
  37         name=None,  # type: Optional[str]
  38     ):
  39         # type (...) -> List[PathEntry]
  40         version_matcher = operator.methodcaller(
  41             "matches", major, minor, patch, pre, dev, arch, python_name=name
  42         )
  43         pythons = [py for py in self.version_list if version_matcher(py)]
  44         version_sort = operator.attrgetter("version_sort")
  45         return [
  46             c.comes_from for c in sorted(pythons, key=version_sort, reverse=True)
  47             if c.comes_from
  48         ]
  49 
  50     def find_python_version(
  51         self,
  52         major=None,  # type: Optional[Union[str, int]]
  53         minor=None,  # type: Optional[int]
  54         patch=None,  # type: Optional[int]
  55         pre=None,  # type: Optional[bool]
  56         dev=None,  # type: Optional[bool]
  57         arch=None,  # type: Optional[str]
  58         name=None,  # type: Optional[str]
  59     ):
  60         # type: (...) -> Optional[PathEntry]
  61         return next(
  62             iter(
  63                 v
  64                 for v in self.find_all_python_versions(
  65                     major=major,
  66                     minor=minor,
  67                     patch=patch,
  68                     pre=pre,
  69                     dev=dev,
  70                     arch=arch,
  71                     name=name,
  72                 )
  73             ),
  74             None,
  75         )
  76 
  77     @_versions.default
  78     def get_versions(self):
  79         # type: () -> DefaultDict[Tuple, PathEntry]
  80         versions = defaultdict(PathEntry)  # type: DefaultDict[Tuple, PathEntry]
  81         from pythonfinder._vendor.pep514tools import environment as pep514env
  82 
  83         env_versions = pep514env.findall()
  84         path = None
  85         for version_object in env_versions:
  86             install_path = getattr(version_object.info, "install_path", None)
  87             name = getattr(version_object, "tag", None)
  88             company = getattr(version_object, "company", None)
  89             if install_path is None:
  90                 continue
  91             try:
  92                 path = ensure_path(install_path.__getattr__(""))
  93             except AttributeError:
  94                 continue
  95             try:
  96                 py_version = PythonVersion.from_windows_launcher(
  97                     version_object, name=name, company=company
  98                 )
  99             except InvalidPythonVersion:
 100                 continue
 101             if py_version is None:
 102                 continue
 103             self.version_list.append(py_version)
 104             python_path = (
 105                 py_version.comes_from.path
 106                 if py_version.comes_from
 107                 else py_version.executable
 108             )
 109             python_kwargs = {python_path: py_version} if python_path is not None else {}
 110             base_dir = PathEntry.create(
 111                 path, is_root=True, only_python=True, pythons=python_kwargs
 112             )
 113             versions[py_version.version_tuple[:5]] = base_dir
 114             self.paths.append(base_dir)
 115         return versions
 116 
 117     @property
 118     def versions(self):
 119         # type: () -> DefaultDict[Tuple, PathEntry]
 120         if not self._versions:
 121             self._versions = self.get_versions()
 122         return self._versions
 123 
 124     @_pythons.default
 125     def get_pythons(self):
 126         # type: () -> DefaultDict[str, PathEntry]
 127         pythons = defaultdict()  # type: DefaultDict[str, PathEntry]
 128         for version in self.version_list:
 129             _path = ensure_path(version.comes_from.path)
 130             pythons[_path.as_posix()] = version.comes_from
 131         return pythons
 132 
 133     @property
 134     def pythons(self):
 135         # type: () -> DefaultDict[str, PathEntry]
 136         return self._pythons
 137 
 138     @pythons.setter
 139     def pythons(self, value):
 140         # type: (DefaultDict[str, PathEntry]) -> None
 141         self._pythons = value

 143     @classmethod
 144     def create(cls, *args, **kwargs):
 145         # type: (Type[FinderType], Any, Any) -> FinderType
 146         return cls()
